{{Quote|I'm guessing the Sith weren't a modest people, judging from the sculptures and reliefs lining the canyon walls. They're all different, and the scale doesn't give me any idea how big these people really were.|Captain Naz Felyood commenting on the valley|<ref name="SWG" />}}
The '''Valley of Golg''' was one of many burial valleys constructed on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] by the ancient [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith species]]<ref name="SWG" /> at some point long before around [[200,000 BBY]].<ref name="Date" /> The valley was particularly notable for containing the [[Dathka Graush's tomb|tomb]] of [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[King/Legends|King]] [[Dathka Graush]].<ref name="SWG" />

As recorded by ''[[Jen'jidai]]'' [[Sorzus Syn]] in [[Sorzus Syn's chronicle|her 6900 BBY chronicle]], the monuments in the Valley of Golg stood long before the advent of the [[Zhell/Legends|Zhell]] civilization on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="BoS">''[[Book of Sith: Secrets from the Dark Side]]''</ref>

